

Personal Finance Manager

Description
Personal Finance Manager is a web application designed to help users manage their finances effectively. With features such as expense tracking, budgeting tools, and financial goal setting, it empowers users to take control of their financial health and achieve their financial goals.

Features
Expense Tracking: Easily track your expenses by categorizing transactions and monitoring your spending habits.
Budgeting Tools: Set up budgets for different expense categories and receive notifications when you exceed your budget.
Financial Goal Setting: Define short-term and long-term financial goals, track your progress, and receive personalized recommendations to achieve them.
Secure Authentication: Secure user authentication and authorization system to protect user data and ensure privacy.
Intuitive User Interface: User-friendly interface with interactive charts and graphs for better visualization of financial data.
Technologies Used
Frontend:
React: JavaScript library for building user interfaces
React Router: Declarative routing for React applications
CSS: Styling the user interface
Axios: Promise-based HTTP client for making API requests
Backend:
Node.js: JavaScript runtime environment
Express.js: Web application framework for Node.js
SQLite: Lightweight relational database management system
Sequelize: Promise-based ORM for Node.js
JWT (JSON Web Tokens): Secure method for transmitting information between parties